 given but something that each of us is responsible for producing. Engaging with many central figures in modern European thought, this book will appeal to philosophers and historians of European philosophy, scholars of modern Christianity, and those working on problems at the intersection of religion and modernity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAsceticism. 0aExistentialism. 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh  aJean-Paul Sartre.  aMartin Heidegger.  aSoren Kierkegaard.  aascetic.  aauthenticity.  aconversion.  aexistentialism.  aphenomenology.  apietism.  asecular.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831107109840 cprintz978022640451640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226404653423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226404653/original  a978-3-11-071098-4  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles